s mehrsprachige Individuen verorten. Open Access:Die freie Verfügbarkeit der E-Book-Ausgabe dieser Publikation wurde im Juli 2019 nachträglich ermöglicht durch den Fachinformationsdienst Linguistik.https://www.linguistik.de/  aThis study examines statements about language attitudes expressed by bilingually raised Germans of Vietnamese origin during language biographical interviews in search of specific conversational features. A further focus of the research is on the linguistic construction of different "language spaces" in which the interviewees position themselves as multilingual individuals.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aKonversationsanalyse. 4aMehrsprachigkeit. 4aSpracheinstellung. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aConversational Analysis.  aLanguage Attitude.  aMultilingualism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2014z9783110370270oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831103771490 cprintz978311035171240uhttps://doi.org/10.1524/9783110352245zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110352245zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110352245/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-DLSc2000d2014  aZDB-23-DSPb2014  aZDB-23-GOA